module of a carry-lookahead 32-bit adder that uses the Carry-Lookahead Adder (CLA) architecture.

Module name:  
    adder_32bit               
Input ports:
    A[32:1]: 32-bit input operand A.
    B[32:1]: 32-bit input operand B.
Output ports:
    S[32:1]: 32-bit output representing the sum of A and B.
    C32: Carry-out output.

Implementation:
The top module adder_32bit consists of several instances of the 16 bit CLA block you design.

Give me the complete code.

```verilog
module adder_32bit
(
    input [32:1] A,
    input [32:1] B,
    output [32:1] S,
    output C32
);
    // Declare internal wires
    wire C16, C32;
    wire [15:0] S_low, S_high;
    wire [15:0] A_low, A_high, B_low, B_high;
    // Instantiate low and high 16-bit CLA modules
    cla_16bit low_cla (
        .A(A[15:1]),
        .B(B[15:1]),
        .Cin(1'b0),
        .S(S_low),
        .Cout(C16)
    );
    cla_16bit high_cla (
        .A(A[31:16]),
        .B(B[31:16]),
        .Cin(C16),
        .S(S_high),
        .Cout(C32)
    );
    // Assign low 16-bit output
    assign S[15:1] = S_low;
    // Assign high 16-bit output
    assign S[32:16] = S_high;
    // Assign carry-out
    assign C32 = C32;
endmodule
